frameDefinitions: This frame covers LUs that describe the race of a Person.
An Agent actively (yet not always with success) attempts to keep themselves from participating in an Event.

In this frame a Hindrance makes it more difficult for a Protagonist to complete their intended Action or a Hindrance directly affects an Action where the Action can be a natural act or the actions of many individuals in a collective endeavor.
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to continue.
A Potential_hindrance or an Agent (via their actions) keeps an Event from taking place, or despite the possibility of prevent the Event, do not do so.
An Activity takes some Time_length to complete.
frameExamples: Carlos is <t>hispanic</t>, or so he says.
Malcolm was <t>hindered</t> by his drinking problem .
The goaltenders <t>kept</t> the game going with terrific saves.
Rain <t>prevented</t> the ball game from taking place.
listRoleDefinitions: The Person whose race is being described.
The Agent who tries to keep an Event from taking place.
The Event is the action or state of affairs that the Agent wishes to prevent.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Agent</fen> prevents the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place </fen> is where the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to prevent the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the entity that tends towards or plans some <fen>Action</fen> which the <fen>Hindrance</fen> causes to be more difficult.
The <fen>Hindrance</fen> is the force which makes the <fen>Action</fen> more difficult or less likely to be successfully completed. The <fen>Hindrance</fen> may be a lack of enabling force:

The <fen>Action</fen> is what the <fen>Protagonist</fen> desires to do, which is made more difficult by the <fen>Hindrance</fen>. It can also be a natural act or collective endeavor, not linked to an overt <fen>Protagonist</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Hindrance</fen> affects the <fen>Protagonist</fen> or <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location where  he <fen>Hindrance</fen> affects the <fen>Protagonist</fen> or <fen>Action</fen>.
The individual who causes the <fen>Process</fen> to continue or the <fen>State</fen> to be maintained.
A <fen>Process</fen> that is maintained by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The <fen>State</fen> that is maintained by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
An event that causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to be maintained.
The time at which the <fen>Process</fen> continues.
The location at which the <fen>Process</fen> continues.
The <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> is the force which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening, or does not.
The <fen>Event</fen> is prevented from occurring by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen> or the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the sentient being which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> or <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> or <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The event which requires some <fen>Time_length</fen> for completion.
The amount of time required for the <fen>Activity</fen>.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Time_length</fen> from the norm.
The individual who performs the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Activity</fen> takes place.
listRoleExamples: The project was hampered <fex>by a lack of funds</fex>.
The soot in the air  kept <fex>it</fex> <fex>raining</fex> for weeks
<fex>The storm</fex> kept us in all the next day.
